<TITLE> Anglo Irish Bank sees EPS growth on target at 15 pct </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DUBLIN, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Anglo Irish Bank said on Friday it expected earnings this year to grow in line with the consensus of market forecasts of a 15 percent rise after a "strong" first four months of its business year. Shares in the bank, which had fallen 14 percent so far this year as global market turmoil compounded fears over the impact of a slowing Irish economy, rallied following the statement and were up 4.8 percent at 9.85 euros by 1045 GMT. Core profits had increased "appreciably" during the first four months of its business year, Chairman Sean FitzPatrick told shareholders at the company's annual meeting, and the bank had seen continued growth in customer lending and funding. "(That) allows us to reaffirm 2008 guidance in line with current market consensus of 15 percent growth in earnings per share," he said. "Your board looks forward to continued above-market performance over the medium and long-term." Anglo Irish Bank had said at the time of its full-year results in November that it expected underlying earnings per share growth of "in excess of 15 percent" in the year to the end of September 2008. The average of 18 forecasts compiled by Reuters Estimates showed analysts currently expect a 14.5 percent rise this ye
